listings.title: Memory Makeover With Daniel Amen, MD
listings.description: Dr. Daniel Amen explains the causes of memory loss, the seven foods and supplements that may enhance memory and how to supercharge memory with 11 simple daily practices.

listings.title: The Highwaymen Live at Nassau Coliseum
listings.description: Willie Nelson, Waylon Jennings, Johnny Cash and Kris Kristofferson perform their hits in this 1990 concert at the Nassau Coliseum; songs include "Big River," "Me and Bobby McGee" and "Always on My Mind."

listings.title: Kris Kristofferson: Life & Songs
listings.description: A 2016 concert celebrates Kris Kristofferson; performers include Dierks Bentley, Rosanne Cash, Eric Church, Emmylou Harris, Jamey Johnson, Alison Krauss, Lady A, Martina McBride, Reba McEntire, Willie Nelson and more.

listings.title: Happy Yoga With Sarah Starr
listings.description: Yoga can be challenging, especially for beginners who may be apprehensive about trying something that they think is too daunting. Wanting to help those who are new to the exercise, fitness instructor Sarah Starr created an easier routine. Happy Yoga, as she calls it, is a modified program using chairs that allows people of any age or physical condition to be able to benefit from yoga. "Happy Yoga" features Starr performing the chair exercises outside, utilizing serene backdrops that showcase Mother Nature's beauty.
listings.episode_description: Stretching the hands, wrists, shoulders, upper back and legs.

listings.title: Classical Stretch: By Essentrics
listings.description: Miranda Esmonde-White offers an exercise program for people of all ages and fitness levels.
listings.episode_description: Increasing bone strength with an all-standing workout.

listings.title: Cyberchase
listings.description: After being warped into Cyberspace from a library computer, Matt leads friends Jackie and Inez as Cybersquad. With live hosts Bianca and Harry, the team must protect Motherboard from the evil Hacker who wants to rule Cyberspace. Using gadgets and following clues, the team solves math mysteries and any other problem that comes their way.
listings.episode_description: Jackie wins a chance to apprentice with fashion designer Fabio DeZine and learns it takes more than a pretty drawing to design something that makes a sustaining impact.

listings.title: Wild Kratts
listings.description: This show follows the adventures of animated versions of brothers Chris and Martin Kratt, hosts of such educational shows as "Kratts' Creatures" and "Zoboomafoo." In the show, the animated Kratts encounter wild animals during stories of adventure and mystery. The live-action Kratt brothers introduce each episode.
listings.episode_description: Martin and Chris befriend a female white shark.

listings.title: Lyla in the Loop
listings.episode_title: Operation Rise and Shine; The Carrot Cake Dance
listings.description: Seven-year-old Lyla and her close-knit family address everyday problems together in the big city.
listings.episode_description: Lyla and her siblings figure out a new morning routine so they won't miss the bus again; Lyla wants to learn a popular clap and dance sequence -- the Carrot Cake dance.

listings.title: Carl the Collector
listings.episode_title: The Sticker Collection; The Baby Stuff Collection
listings.description: The everyday adventures of Carl, an autistic raccoon, who loves collecting things.
listings.episode_description: Carl's favorite sour pickle scratch-n-sniff sticker loses its smell; Carl notices that his baby blanket, Knit-Knit, has a hole in it.

listings.title: Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood
listings.description: The first series inspired by "Mister Rogers Neighborhood," "Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood" features 4-year-old Daniel Tiger, son of the original program's Daniel Striped Tiger. Every day Daniel puts on his red sweater, ties his shoes, and invites a new generation of preschoolers into the Neighborhood of Make-Believe. Daniel shares his daily adventures with pals O the Owl, Katerina Kittycat, Prince Wednesday and Miss Elaina. With the help of Daniel and his friends, preschoolers have fun and learn practical skills necessary for growing and developing.
listings.episode_description: Volunteer firefighters make a special visit to school; Daniel wants to pretend to be the daddy when he gets a new doll, but his friends want him to be Tige-y the Adventure Tiger instead.

listings.title: Rosie's Rules
listings.description: Five-year-old Mexican American Rosie Fuentes learns how the world around her works in her suburban Texas community.
listings.episode_description: The Fuentes kids make a fort in the living room but disagree about what to put in it; Rosie and Javi build a car for a derby race.

listings.title: Sesame Street
listings.description: A longtime favorite of children and adults, and a staple of PBS, "Sesame Street" bridges many cultural and educational gaps with a fun program. Big Bird leads a cast of characters teaching children numbers, colors and the alphabet. Bert and Ernie, Oscar the Grouch and Grover are just a few of the other creatures involved in this show, set on a city street full of valuable learning opportunities.
listings.episode_description: Elmo shares his scooter with Zoe and learns how to be patient and wait for his turn, while she practices and learns how to ride.

listings.title: Work It Out Wombats!
listings.episode_title: The Kaya-tastic Banana-tastic Halo Halo Split!; Amazing Adventure
listings.description: A playful trio of marsupial siblings look for interesting problems to solve in their Treeborhood.
listings.episode_description: Kaya's cooking class; the Wombats go on a treasure hunt.

listings.title: Donkey Hodie
listings.description: Donkey Hodie and her pals follow their dreams and work together to find creative solutions to everyday problems.
listings.episode_description: A noisy penguin interrupts band practice; the pals work together to win Gator's latest game show.

listings.title: Pinkalicious & Peterrific
listings.description: The creative adventures of Pinkalicious and her brother, Peter.
listings.episode_description: Pinkalicious helps Rafael train his dog for the Pinkminster Dog Show; Mommy's invention, the Do-Over Ray, gives people the chance to try something again if they mess up.

listings.title: Elinor Wonders Why
listings.description: The adventures of an observant and curious bunny rabbit named Elinor and her friends Ari the bat and Olive the elephant.
listings.episode_description: Ari and Olive make Elinor's favorite snack, backyard soup, when she is stuck at home after hurting her foot; Elinor becomes fascinated with dandelions.

listings.title: Alma's Way
listings.episode_title: Alma's Rescue Repair; Alma Cools Off
listings.description: Six-year old Alma, a Puerto Rican girl who lives with her family in the Bronx, learns to think for herself, making mistakes and finding solutions along the way.
listings.episode_description: Alma opens a traveling repair service, but running back and forth for fix-it supplies proves exhausting; Alma has to figure out how to handle her feelings when Howard tells Junior he can't play water tag.

listings.title: Molly of Denali
listings.description: The daily adventures of 10-year-old Alaska native Molly Mabray, her family, her dog Suki and her friends Tooey and Trini.
listings.episode_description: Molly and Trini look for firewood to make treats, but plans are interrupted by a storm; Molly and Tooey hope to teach Trini how to skate in time for the River Skate and bonfire.

listings.title: Xavier Riddle and the Secret Museum
listings.episode_title: I Am Kate Warne; I Am Sir Arthur Conan Doyle
listings.description: Xavier Riddle, his sister, Yadina, and their friend, Brad, meet heroes from the past -- from Eleanor Roosevelt to Leonardo da Vinci.
listings.episode_description: Brad gives up on hide-and-seek until Kate Warne helps him figure out how to play the game better; Sir Arthur Conan Doyle helps Xavier decide what to get the new girl in class for her birthday.

listings.title: Sit and Be Fit
listings.description: Mary Ann Wilson leads safe workouts set to fun music.
listings.episode_description: An energetic workout focuses on shoulder range of motion and improving head-eye coordination; a calming visual relaxation.

listings.title: Classical Stretch: By Essentrics
listings.description: Miranda Esmonde-White offers an exercise program for people of all ages and fitness levels.
listings.episode_description: Increasing bone strength with an all-standing workout.

listings.title: Classical Rewind (My Music Presents)
listings.description: A visual and auditory look at classical masterpieces; host Martin Goldsmith.

listings.title: Why You Like It: Decoding Musical Taste
listings.description: Composer and musicologist Dr. Nolan Gasser presents an immersive program that explores the science and culture behind musical preferences, blending live performances, animations and insights from neuroscience, psychology, culture and more.

listings.title: BBC News America
listings.description: Live news program produced out of BBC's Washington, D.C. bureau; host Sumi Somaskanda.

listings.title: BBC News The Context
listings.description: A regular panel of guests from across the political spectrum discuss the biggest international stories of the day, along with news-making interviews and analysis from BBC correspondents around the globe.

listings.title: PBS News Hour
listings.description: Co-anchors Amna Nawaz and Geoff Bennett and correspondents offer in-depth analysis of current events.
listings.episode_description: Co-anchors Amna Nawaz and Geoff Bennett and correspondents offer in-depth analysis of current events.

listings.title: Henry Louis Gates, Jr. -- The Fabric of America
listings.description: A retrospective look at cultural historian Henry Louis Gates Jr. and how his work has made history come alive for millions of Americans.

listings.title: Women of World War II: The Untold Stories
listings.description: The stories of women who helped win World War II, including those who risked their lives flying planes, served as American spies and in the all-African American Central Postal battalion.

listings.title: Ken Burns: The National Parks
listings.description: Filmmakers Ken Burns and Dayton Duncan reveal behind-the-scenes stories about the making of "The National Parks: America's Best Idea."

listings.title: Simply Ming
listings.description: Acclaimed chef Ming Tsai is known for his melding of Eastern and Western flavors, a theme he furthers in "Simply Ming." Each episode deals with a specific staple, what he refers to as a Master Recipe. He demonstrates how to make that one staple, then he shares recipes that use that particular staple. Whether it's a bittersweet chocolate ganache, from which he creates souffle cakes and an Asian banana split, or flavorful chicken broth he then uses to prepare ginger-poached chicken breast and hot and sour shrimp soup, the chef shares recipes and tricks for the beginning cook as well as the accomplished kitchen pro.
listings.episode_description: Cooking maki rolls with toasted nori, fish, poached shrimp and avocado; a sake royal made with junmai sake and cassis; a non-alcoholic cassis-lime spritzer.

listings.title: Cook's Country
listings.description: Hosts Bridget Lancaster and Julia Collin Davison offer a practical, no-nonsense and scientific approach to making a wide range of American recipes, from barbecue chicken thighs to Mississippi mud pie to parmesan potatoes. The hosts are joined by test cooks Ashley Moore, Bryan Roof, Christie Morrison, Lawman Johnson, and Natalie Estrada. Episodes include equipment recommendations for the home cook, taste tests and origins for new recipes such as Southern-style smothered chicken, grilled bourbon steaks and many more.
listings.episode_description: Transylvania goulash; heirloom beans; shredded Swiss chard salad; escarole; beans and greens.

listings.title: Pati's Mexican Table
listings.description: Chef Pati Jinich introduces authentic Mexican flavors, colors and textures into American kitchens. Each episode features a single Mexican food, ranging from familiar ingredients like vanilla to mysterious grains used by the Aztecs. Season 8 explores simple and delectable dishes from both Mexico and the United States, including street food, a seafood feast, taco recipes, lobster recipes, and a breakfast based on Sinaloan classics.
listings.episode_description: A lesson in roping and riding from rodeo champion Ricardo "Bubba" Nevárez; carne asada; cattle rancher Alvaro Bustillos; serving up some cowboy delicacies.

listings.title: Pati's Mexican Table
listings.description: Chef Pati Jinich introduces authentic Mexican flavors, colors and textures into American kitchens. Each episode features a single Mexican food, ranging from familiar ingredients like vanilla to mysterious grains used by the Aztecs. Season 8 explores simple and delectable dishes from both Mexico and the United States, including street food, a seafood feast, taco recipes, lobster recipes, and a breakfast based on Sinaloan classics.
listings.episode_description: Culinary highlights of Guadalajara, capital of Jalisco, Mexico; tortas ahogadas; chef Fabian Delgado sets new expectations for the market food experience.

listings.title: Baking With Julia
listings.description: Julia Child hosts a how-to cooking show with the country's top pastry chefs, bakers, teachers and cookbook authors. Each expert visits Julia in her kitchen to demonstrate how to make his or her signature creation, providing techniques, tips and recipes.
listings.episode_description: Steve Sullivan prepares walnut bread; decorative loaves.

listings.title: New Scandinavian Cooking
listings.description: "New Scandinavian Cooking" is a culinary show that isn't filmed in a kitchen or TV studio, which is common with most shows of the genre. The series is filmed on a variety of locations throughout Scandinavia, offering a visual tour of Northern European cuisine, culture and history. In each episode, recipes are prepared featuring locally sourced ingredients, ranging from berries and mushrooms to cod and mussels.
listings.episode_description: Baked trout with herbs wrapped in cured ham; grilled sirloin with vinegar butter and burnt lemon; mutton sausages with mustard-marinated potatoes.

listings.title: This Old House
listings.episode_title: Ridgewood: Flooring Features and a Rocking Fountain
listings.description: This Emmy-winning home-improvement series takes the mystery and fright factors out of remodeling and carpentry chores.
listings.episode_description: Tile for a curbless shower; installing the kitchen floors; installing a custom-made water feature for the backyard patio.

listings.title: Ask This Old House
listings.description: Created by viewer demand, the series is a spinoff of "This Old House" and answers specific remodeling questions that viewers send in. The cast includes host Kevin O'Connor, general contractor Tom Silva, heating/plumbing master Richard Trethewey and landscaper Roger Cook, who spend the hour focusing on various topics for the do-it-yourself homeowner.
listings.episode_description: Painting wainscoting; what homeowners should know before switching a home to all electric; building a sandbox.

listings.title: Rick Steves' Europe
listings.description: Rick Steves' guidebooks, public-radio program and numerous television series have made him an essential resource for travelers wishing to explore Europe. This program finds the knowledgeable host offering globetrotters a fresh perspective on lodgings, transportation and places to visit on their journeys. One thing that hasn't changed, however, is Steves' belief that travelers should become "temporary locals," exploring not only major cities and the usual sites, but out-of-the-way locales that often produce the most authentic, and enjoyable, experiences of a trip.
listings.episode_description: The Trastevere district's historic Jewish Ghetto; churches.

listings.title: The Best of the Joy of Painting
listings.description: This series of episodes culled from the vast library of the late Bob Ross ("The Joy of Painting") features the soft-spoken host sharing his painting techniques, including his "wet-on-wet" technique, and creating some of his best-loved scenes. From a cabin in the majestic mountains or a covered bride to an owl in a country barn or an autumnal forest scene, Ross creates a complete work of art in each episode -- many of which feature his trademark "happy little clouds." His soothing tone and words of encouragement inspire those painting along at home, and entrance those just watching to see him create his nature scenes.
listings.episode_description: A frozen stream sits under a covered bridge.

listings.title: P. Allen Smith's Garden Home
listings.description: A garden can be much more than just a place for planting flowers or growing assorted vegetables. Host P. Allen Smith shares his years of expertise and design flair to help viewers create actual garden rooms, which can be used for different functions such as dining, entertaining and playing. These special sanctuaries utilize the best elements of indoor and outdoor spaces that, when blended together, truly create a private paradise. Of course, viewers can also set aside the usual spot for plants and wildlife to flourish.
listings.episode_description: Building a solid foundation in the garden.

listings.title: J Schwanke's Life in Bloom
listings.description: Fourth-generation florist, author and floral educator J Schwanke hosts this series about flower arrangement, design and instruction. Aiming to help viewers have fun with flowers, the program shows how to incorporate flowers into homes and everyday life. The series also includes tours of flower farms, greenhouses, markets, festivals and special events around the world. Some segments include a visit to a succulent farm, tulip-inspired recipes, using fruit and flowers in arrangements, recipes and crafts and creating an orchid wreath.

listings.description: Miranda Esmonde-White offers an exercise program for people of all ages and fitness levels.

listings.description: Painting on location throughout the U.S.
listings.episode_description: Studio in Clearwater, Fla.

Offering something for everyone, "Quilting Arts" explores art and design concepts for quilts which include surface design techniques, fabric collage and quilted home decor. Episodes include short features that relate to the show's theme and weekly digital segments. Some projects include hand-painting fabrics with silk screening paints, fabric marbling using stencils, and frameless screen printing.
listings.episode_description: Making an improvisational quilt complete with thin strips and odd shapes; adding free-motion quilting and hand embroidery to abstract art quilts.

listings.description: Storyteller and explorer Ernest White II learns about cities and regions from his friends.
listings.episode_description: Flying to New Delhi, India's capital, to make new friends, ride the ricks, play cricket and eat.

listings.title: The Best of the Joy of Painting
listings.description: This series of episodes culled from the vast library of the late Bob Ross ("The Joy of Painting") features the soft-spoken host sharing his painting techniques, including his "wet-on-wet" technique, and creating some of his best-loved scenes. From a cabin in the majestic mountains or a covered bride to an owl in a country barn or an autumnal forest scene, Ross creates a complete work of art in each episode -- many of which feature his trademark "happy little clouds." His soothing tone and words of encouragement inspire those painting along at home, and entrance those just watching to see him create his nature scenes.
listings.episode_description: A Southwest desert.

listings.title: Fresh Glass
listings.description: Stories from diverse innovators in the food and beverage fields.
listings.episode_description: Visiting Valle de Guadalupe and Ensenada in Mexico.

listings.title: Christopher Kimball's Milk Street Television
listings.description: Christopher Kimball demonstrates a bolder yet simpler way of preparing food.
listings.episode_description: Turkish wedding soup; Yucatecan chicken and lime soup; Filipino chicken soup with coconut and lemongrass.

listings.title: Memory Makeover With Daniel Amen, MD
listings.description: Dr. Daniel Amen explains the causes of memory loss, the seven foods and supplements that may enhance memory and how to supercharge memory with 11 simple daily practices.

listings.title: Happy Yoga With Sarah Starr
listings.description: Yoga can be challenging, especially for beginners who may be apprehensive about trying something that they think is too daunting. Wanting to help those who are new to the exercise, fitness instructor Sarah Starr created an easier routine. Happy Yoga, as she calls it, is a modified program using chairs that allows people of any age or physical condition to be able to benefit from yoga. "Happy Yoga" features Starr performing the chair exercises outside, utilizing serene backdrops that showcase Mother Nature's beauty.
listings.episode_description: Stretching the hands, wrists, shoulders, upper back and legs.

listings.episode_description: Increasing bone strength with an all-standing workout.

With live hosts Bianca and Harry, the team must protect Motherboard from the evil Hacker who wants to rule Cyberspace. Using gadgets and following clues, the team solves math mysteries and any other problem that comes their way.
listings.episode_description: Jackie wins a chance to apprentice with fashion designer Fabio DeZine and learns it takes more than a pretty drawing to design something that makes a sustaining impact.

listings.description: The first series inspired by "Mister Rogers Neighborhood," "Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood" features 4-year-old Daniel Tiger, son of the original program's Daniel Striped Tiger. Every day Daniel puts on his red sweater, ties his shoes, and invites a new generation of preschoolers into the Neighborhood of Make-Believe. Daniel shares his daily adventures with pals O the Owl, Katerina Kittycat, Prince Wednesday and Miss Elaina. With the help of Daniel and his friends, preschoolers have fun and learn practical skills necessary for growing and developing.

listings.description: Young government agents Olive and Otto use math to investigate strange occurrences in their town. Odd Squad cases include disappearing zeroes, Santa's missing reindeer, runaway dinosaurs, and characters who escape from books. Throughout the series, Olive and Otto learn not only how to solve problems but also about working together, communication and perseverance.
listings.episode_description: The agents track down missing monuments; the agents must determine who the real Oswald is.

listings.episode_description: Dev needs to stay organized as a laundromat manager to clean the team jerseys; Rae creates an easier way for the Beeples to get to the top of Mount Froyo.

listings.description: This animated series centers on house cat Fred, a dreamer of the great outdoors. Once his family leaves for the day, Fred becomes Nature Cat and with the help of his animal friends, he embarks on action-packed adventures that allow him to explore the natural world. The series is voiced by comic actors, including "Saturday Night Live" alums Taran Killam (Nature Cat), Kate McKinnon (Squeeks), Bobby Moynihan (Hal) and Kenan Thompson (Ronald). Kate Micucci rounds out the cast as Daisy.
listings.episode_description: Nature Cat and pals hike to the top of Mighty Mountain; the pals split up after an argument.

listings.episode_description: Molly, Grandpa, Dad and Tooey go on a snowmobile adventure to search for hot springs in the backwoods; Tooey's hero, dog musher Eugene Pike, re-creates a historic mail run across interior Alaska.

listings.episode_description: Andy and friends get confused while shopping in London, due to differences between British and American English; Luna explains to Andy how sounds of the city help them find their way.

Inspired by the scholastic book series by Norman Bridwell, each episode emphasizes social-emotional skills and a curriculum that promotes early literacy and imaginative play.

From a cabin in the majestic mountains or a covered bride to an owl in a country barn or an autumnal forest scene, Ross creates a complete work of art in each episode -- many of which feature his trademark "happy little clouds." Episodes include equipment recommendations for the home cook, taste tests and origins for new recipes such as Southern-style smothered chicken, grilled bourbon steaks and many more.
listings.episode_description: Japanese steakhouse steak and vegetables; the legacy of the Japanese steakhouse in the U.S.; cast iron skillets; charred cherry tomatoes with bell peppers and mozzarella.

listings.title: America's Test Kitchen From Cook's Illustrated
listings.description: Bridget Lancaster and Julia Collin Davison host a look inside America's Test Kitchen, which features a team of experts who check out the latest in cooking utensils, ingredients and cooking techniques. Whether they're trying to make the perfect roasted chicken with crispy skin or examining the science behind cooking with baking powder, team members try to offer unbiased and useful tips that can save viewers money, time and effort in their own kitchens. The basic team is frequently joined by other test cooks, as well as blind-taste judges.
listings.episode_description: Porchetta; ricotta; wine coolers; Parmesan farrotto.

listings.episode_description: Mosaics; Testaccio food market; cacio e pepe; making gelato; street artist Alice Pasquini; historic ball performed by Campagna Nazionale di Danza Storica.

listings.description: Yoga can be challenging, especially for beginners who may be apprehensive about trying something that they think is too daunting. Wanting to help those who are new to the exercise, fitness instructor Sarah Starr created an easier routine. Happy Yoga, as she calls it, is a modified program using chairs that allows people of any age or physical condition to be able to benefit from yoga. "Happy Yoga" features Starr performing the chair exercises outside, utilizing serene backdrops that showcase Mother Nature's beauty.
listings.episode_description: Flowing warrior series using a chair for support focuses on strengthening the legs and opening the hips, shoulders and upper back.

Using gadgets and following clues, the team solves math mysteries and any other problem that comes their way.
listings.episode_description: The team uses logic to free the Lucky Charms from Hacker's control.

Daniel shares his daily adventures with pals O the Owl, Katerina Kittycat, Prince Wednesday and Miss Elaina. With the help of Daniel and his friends, preschoolers have fun and learn practical skills necessary for growing and developing.
listings.episode_description: Daniel and his parents have a sleepover at Prince Wednesday's castle; O the Owl is hesitant to camp in the yard.

One thing that hasn't changed, however, is Steves' belief that travelers should become "temporary locals," exploring not only major cities and the usual sites, but out-of-the-way locales that often produce the most authentic, and enjoyable, experiences of a trip.

From a cabin in the majestic mountains or a covered bride to an owl in a country barn or an autumnal forest scene, Ross creates a complete work of art in each episode -- many of which feature his trademark "happy little clouds." listings.episode_description: Making a travel trio bag set; a jewels and treats bag; curling iron tote; a tee with secret pockets for valuables.

listings.title: America's Test Kitchen From Cook's Illustrated
listings.description: Bridget Lancaster and Julia Collin Davison host a look inside America's Test Kitchen, which features a team of experts who check out the latest in cooking utensils, ingredients and cooking techniques. Whether they're trying to make the perfect roasted chicken with crispy skin or examining the science behind cooking with baking powder, team members try to offer unbiased and useful tips that can save viewers money, time and effort in their own kitchens. The basic team is frequently joined by other test cooks, as well as blind-taste judges.
listings.episode_description: Test cook Lan Lam makes Bridget the ultimate grilled mojo-marinated skirt steak. Test cook Keith Dresser and host Julia reveal the secrets to the best Peruvian ceviche recipe.

listings.title: Ciao Italia
listings.description: Recipes for great Italian cooking.
listings.episode_description: Preparing a traditional rustic cake from the Abruzzo region of Italy -- the Abruzzese ricotta cake.

listings.title: America's Test Kitchen From Cook's Illustrated

listings.episode_description: Three cup chicken; firm tofu; smashed cucumbers.

listings.title: Cycle Around Japan Highlights
listings.description: Discovering Japan by bicycle, exploring a side of Japan not found in guidebooks.
listings.episode_description: Discovering Japan by bicycle, exploring a side of Japan not found in guidebooks.

listings.title: Samantha Brown's Places to Love
listings.description: Samantha Brown explores the emotional heart of travel and the people who change, challenge and strengthen a destination.
listings.episode_description: The Living Desert Zoo and Gardens; stunt driving; Shields Date Garden; pollinating date trees; date shake; Joshua Tree National Park.

listings.title: Rick Steves' Europe
listings.description: Rick Steves' guidebooks, public-radio program and numerous television series have made him an essential resource for travelers wishing to explore Europe. This program finds the knowledgeable host offering globetrotters a fresh perspective on lodgings, transportation and places to visit on their journeys. One thing that hasn't changed, however, is Steves' belief that travelers should become "temporary locals," exploring not only major cities and the usual sites, but out-of-the-way locales that often produce the most authentic, and enjoyable, experiences of a trip.
listings.episode_description: Cluny Museum; midnight ride in a classic car; stained glass in Sainte-Chapelle; Père Lachaise Cemetery; Parisian cafes.

listings.title: Fresh Glass
listings.description: Stories from diverse innovators in the food and beverage fields.
listings.episode_description: Cassandra and her cast share insights about taking risks, understanding the hustle and betting on yourself.

listings.title: Sara's Weeknight Meals
listings.description: Chef, cookbook author and TV host Sara Moulton presents helpful hints for preparing quick and easy healthy meals at home. Episodes feature ideas for Sunday suppers, for one-pot meals, and for preparing flavor-packed meals using only five ingredients. Some recipes include pork tournedos with sage and prosciutto, steamed mussels in curried coconut broth, a fried-catfish bacon/lettuce/tomato sandwich, and a salad of grilled-salmon, arugula and grilled corn.
listings.episode_description: Spaghetti with bacon and eggs; meatloaf made in individual portions with spiced peas and onions on the side.

listings.title: Cook's Country
listings.description: Hosts Bridget Lancaster and Julia Collin Davison offer a practical, no-nonsense and scientific approach to making a wide range of American recipes, from barbecue chicken thighs to Mississippi mud pie to parmesan potatoes. The hosts are joined by test cooks Ashley Moore, Bryan Roof, Christie Morrison, Lawman Johnson, and Natalie Estrada. Episodes include equipment recommendations for the home cook, taste tests and origins for new recipes such as Southern-style smothered chicken, grilled bourbon steaks and many more.
listings.episode_description: Banana pudding pie; different vanilla products; the story of Augustus Jackson's eggless ice cream; no-churn ice cream.

listings.title: Ireland With Michael
listings.episode_title: May the Road Rise to Meet You
listings.description: Michael Londra travels around Ireland, celebrating its culture, history and music.
listings.episode_description: The mystic past of Lough Erne; musicians Nathan Carter, Niamh Dunne and Sean Og Graham; a gin distillery.

listings.title: Family Travel With Colleen Kelly
listings.episode_title: Family Travel on the Emerald Isle -- Ireland as a Family Getaway
listings.description: Host and travel guide Colleen Kelly visits must-see destinations and family-friendly attractions throughout the United States and abroad. Designed to help families with vacation planning, each 30-minute episode offers behind-the-scenes tours that cover local culture and history, kid-friendly attractions and activities as well as family-friendly places to stay. From big cities such as Chicago and Los Angeles to international destinations like Ireland and Montreal, this series covers all the bases of vacation planning for families of all ages.
listings.episode_description: Journeying through Ireland's Wild Atlantic Way; zip lining through the Delphi Forest; birds of prey at Dromoland Castle; herding sheep and feeding lambs at Glen Keen Farm.

listings.title: Ireland With Michael
listings.description: Michael Londra travels around Ireland, celebrating its culture, history and music.
listings.episode_description: The Little Cheese Shop; Murphy's Ice Cream; Sea Safari; Inch Beach, home of Arctic explorer Tom Crean; Irish dancer David Geaney; Dingle Whiskey; Irish musician Joanie Madden.

listings.title: Joseph Rosendo's Travelscope
listings.description: This Emmy Award-winning series continues to excite viewers with adventures around the globe, from North America to Africa to Asia. Host Joseph Rosendo embarks on everything from town and country experiences in Portland, Maine, to a cruise down the Rideau Canal in Ottawa, Canada. Other segments feature the Taroko Gorge in Taiwan, Bangkok and the River Kwai in Thailand, and the South Luangwa National Park in Zambia.
listings.episode_description: Exploring Ireland, from Dublin and the Ancient East to Belfast and the Wild Atlantic Way.

listings.title: Ireland With Michael
listings.description: Michael Londra travels around Ireland, celebrating its culture, history and music.
listings.episode_description: The Celtic band Clannad; a walking tour around Derry; sampling scones; Riverdance singer Denise O'Cain.

listings.title: Travelscope
listings.description: Journalist Joseph Rosendo likes to recall a quote from Mark Twain at the end of each episode of his Emmy Award-winning television series: "Travel is fatal to prejudice, bigotry, and narrow-mindedness." Embracing that philosophy, "Travelscope" leads viewers on journeys to the world's most exotic locations with the goal of filling in the missing link between cultures. Rosendo provides not only insights on the numerous places he explores, but important travel information for the conscientious globe-trotter.
listings.episode_description: Dingle Peninsula; Puck Fair in Killorglin on the Ring of Kerry; Blasket Islanders.

listings.title: Ireland With Michael
listings.description: Michael Londra travels around Ireland, celebrating its culture, history and music.
listings.episode_description: King John's Castle; the future Ryder Cup course on Adare Manor estate; crafting Irish coffee at the historic Foynes Flying Boat Museum; a Hollywood movie star's affection for a quaint village.

listings.title: Bare Feet With Mickela Mallozzi
listings.description: Travel host and producer Mickela Mallozzi explores dance and music culture around the world. A professional dancer, Mallozzi begins her journey in her hometown of Minturno, Italy, where she visits the town's annual wheat harvest festival. Other episodes include dancing tango in Buenos Aires, Argentina; South Korea's Jeju Fire Festival; the dance and music traditions of Croatia's Dalmation Coast; cooking and dancing with the indigenous people of Malaysia's eastern regions; and dancing the Viennese Waltz in Vienna.
listings.episode_description: Dancing with some of the "Riverdance" cast in Dublin; the 160-year-old Matchmaking Festival in Lisdoonvarna, Country Clare.

listings.title: Ken Burns: The National Parks
listings.description: Filmmakers Ken Burns and Dayton Duncan reveal behind-the-scenes stories about the making of "The National Parks: America's Best Idea."

listings.title: Young Forever With Mark Hyman, MD
listings.description: Dr. Mark Hyman explores the biological hallmarks of aging, their causes and their consequences and how to overcome them with simple dietary and lifestyle strategies.

listings.title: Happy Yoga With Sarah Starr
listings.description: Yoga can be challenging, especially for beginners who may be apprehensive about trying something that they think is too daunting. Wanting to help those who are new to the exercise, fitness instructor Sarah Starr created an easier routine. Happy Yoga, as she calls it, is a modified program using chairs that allows people of any age or physical condition to be able to benefit from yoga. "Happy Yoga" features Starr performing the chair exercises outside, utilizing serene backdrops that showcase Mother Nature's beauty.
listings.episode_description: A yoga practice focuses on coordinating movement and breath and improving circulation in the upper body.

listings.title: Classical Stretch: By Essentrics
listings.description: Miranda Esmonde-White offers an exercise program for people of all ages and fitness levels.
listings.episode_description: An all-standing workout improves balance, flexibility and mobility.

listings.title: Cyberchase
listings.description: After being warped into Cyberspace from a library computer, Matt leads friends Jackie and Inez as Cybersquad. With live hosts Bianca and Harry, the team must protect Motherboard from the evil Hacker who wants to rule Cyberspace. Using gadgets and following clues, the team solves math mysteries and any other problem that comes their way.
listings.episode_description: Hacker traps Digit and the kids in one of the Spheres of Fears to allow Delete to impersonate Motherboard and cause chaos everywhere.

listings.title: Wild Kratts
listings.description: This show follows the adventures of animated versions of brothers Chris and Martin Kratt, hosts of such educational shows as "Kratts' Creatures" and "Zoboomafoo." In the show, the animated Kratts encounter wild animals during stories of adventure and mystery. The live-action Kratt brothers introduce each episode.
listings.episode_description: A miniaturized Chris gets stuck to a bee.

listings.episode_title: Un-make a Mess; Hide and Go Stu
listings.description: Seven-year-old Lyla and her close-knit family address everyday problems together in the big city.
listings.episode_description: Lyla and Luke clean their room with help from Stu; Stu learns how to play hide-and-seek.

listings.title: Carl the Collector
listings.episode_title: The Fake Mustache Collection; The Lint Dinosaur Collection
listings.description: The everyday adventures of Carl, an autistic raccoon, who loves collecting things.
listings.episode_description: Nico is tired of being mistaken for her twin sister; Carl is upset when Nico breaks the Lint Dinosaur Monday rules and makes a Lint Monster instead.

listings.title: Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood
listings.episode_title: Daniel Gets a Shot; A Stormy Day
listings.description: The first series inspired by "Mister Rogers Neighborhood," "Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood" features 4-year-old Daniel Tiger, son of the original program's Daniel Striped Tiger. Every day Daniel puts on his red sweater, ties his shoes, and invites a new generation of preschoolers into the Neighborhood of Make-Believe. Daniel shares his daily adventures with pals O the Owl, Katerina Kittycat, Prince Wednesday and Miss Elaina. With the help of Daniel and his friends, preschoolers have fun and learn practical skills necessary for growing and developing.
listings.episode_description: Daniel doesn't want to go to the doctor because he has to get a shot; a thunderstorm scares Daniel and O the Owl.

listings.title: Rosie's Rules
listings.description: Five-year-old Mexican American Rosie Fuentes learns how the world around her works in her suburban Texas community.
listings.episode_description: Rosie and Javi transport a watermelon to the park for the family picnic; Rosie builds a dino cave for Iggy.

listings.title: Sesame Street
listings.description: A longtime favorite of children and adults, and a staple of PBS, "Sesame Street" bridges many cultural and educational gaps with a fun program. Big Bird leads a cast of characters teaching children numbers, colors and the alphabet. Bert and Ernie, Oscar the Grouch and Grover are just a few of the other creatures involved in this show, set on a city street full of valuable learning opportunities.
listings.episode_description: Gabrielle tells her friends about Bessie Coleman, the first African-American and Native American woman to fly an airplane; Elmo decides to become the first monster-cook-teacher-cooking teacher.

Odd Squad cases include disappearing zeroes, Santa's missing reindeer, runaway dinosaurs, and characters who escape from books. Throughout the series, Olive and Otto learn not only how to solve problems but also about working together, communication and perseverance.
listings.episode_description: Owen and Ohio provide backup on a case, so they can have a pizza party; an unlucky coin is accidentally released to the public.

listings.title: Eyes on the Prize
listings.description: This landmark series, which first premiered in 1987, documents the history of the civil rights movement in America. Produced by Blackside, segments include the Montgomery bus boycott of 1954, school desegregation in 1957 Arkansas, the right-to-vote battle within Mississippi, the march from Selma to Montgomery, Ala., and the Voting Rights Act of 1965. The series has been honored with a George Foster Peabody Award, an International Documentary Award, Television Critics Association Award and numerous Emmy Awards.

Some segments include an old-time barn dance in North Carolina; the plight of the Native American community around the Isle de Jean Charles in Louisiana; and the career of artist Patrick Dougherty. This anthology series is a collaborative effort between South Carolina ETV, UNC-TV and the Southern Documentary Fund.

Every day Daniel puts on his red sweater, ties his shoes, and invites a new generation of preschoolers into the Neighborhood of Make-Believe. Daniel shares his daily adventures with pals O the Owl, Katerina Kittycat, Prince Wednesday and Miss Elaina. With the help of Daniel and his friends, preschoolers have fun and learn practical skills necessary for growing and developing.
listings.episode_description: Daniel learns that it's important to try to go potty before leaving the house; Daniel learns that sometimes when your tummy hurts, it could mean that you have to go potty.

listings.title: Sesame Street

Bert and Ernie, Oscar the Grouch and Grover are just a few of the other creatures involved in this show, set on a city street full of valuable learning opportunities.
listings.episode_description: Elmo tries to find something to do in the rain, while he waits to jump in the puddles.

listings.episode_description: The Wombats build a Cause and Effect machine; Super's best friend Chanaa pays a visit.

listings.title: Donkey Hodie
listings.description: Donkey Hodie and her pals follow their dreams and work together to find creative solutions to everyday problems.
listings.episode_description: Duck Duck has a big feeling, but she doesn't know what it is; Clyde feels sad, so the pals give him time to feel better.

listings.title: Pinkalicious & Peterrific

listings.description: The creative adventures of Pinkalicious and her brother, Peter.

The basic team is frequently joined by other test cooks, as well as blind-taste judges.

listings.description: Host and travel guide Colleen Kelly visits must-see destinations and family-friendly attractions throughout the United States and abroad. Designed to help families with vacation planning, each 30-minute episode offers behind-the-scenes tours that cover local culture and history, kid-friendly attractions and activities as well as family-friendly places to stay. From big cities such as Chicago and Los Angeles to international destinations like Ireland and Montreal, this series covers all the bases of vacation planning for families of all ages.
listings.episode_description: Journeying through Ireland's Wild Atlantic Way; zip lining through the Delphi Forest; birds of prey at Dromoland Castle; herding sheep and feeding lambs at Glen Keen Farm.

listings.title: No Passport Required
listings.description: This six-episode series hosted by chef Marcus Samuelsson offers viewers a culinary and anthropological exploration of the people, rituals and food of multicultural America. Each week, Marcus visits a new city to learn about how that city made its mark. Featuring musicians, poets, chefs, business owners, artists, community leaders and home cooks, the program spotlights people who have enhanced the nation's culture and cuisine. Some segments include the sights and sounds of Detroit's Arab-American community, how Vietnamese cuisine and culture have influenced New Orleans, and the flavors and heritage of the Haitian community in Miami.
listings.episode_description: The Filipino community in Seattle, including Filipino-American chefs and their influence on the city's food scene.

listings.title: Hidden Ireland
listings.description: Exploring the hidden gems of the Emerald Isle, including Dublin, Cliffs of Moher, Belfast, Ashford Castle and Cape Clear; host Peter Greenberg.

listings.title: Jazzy Vegetarian
listings.description: Laura Theodore presents easy vegetarian cooking to health-conscious viewers of all ages. Basing her healthy meals and snacks on traditional American cuisine, Laura prepares recipes without dairy, meat, eggs or animal products. From festive zucchini lasagna to chocolate desserts, Laura's recipes are also cholesterol-free. Other dishes include sunflower avocado rolls, pasta with broccoli and sun-dried tomatoes, oven-baked Moroccan stew and apple muffins with pumpkin seeds.
listings.episode_description: Oven-baked two-bean chili; potato skins; sweet and salty snack almonds; turtle cookie squares.

listings.description: This award-winning series is a filmed journey of the history, artists and techniques of America's rich craft culture, with a particular focus on its diversity and ever-evolving ways.

listings.episode_title: Curious Rothenburg ob der Tauber, Germany
listings.description: Entertainment journalist Christine van Blokland takes viewers to some of the most intriguing European and North American cities in the world. At each location, viewers get a taste of the art, architecture, museums, monuments, houses of worship and city parks unique to each area. Van Blokland's list of "Curious Questions" sets the tone for each episode, and emphasizes the host's curiosity and quest for knowledge. From London to New York, the series explores the rich culture and mysteries of some of the world's most fascinating destinations.
listings.episode_description: Bavarian storybook architecture; Town Hall; the Meistertrunk legend; St. Jakob's Church and its Reimenschneider altar; medieval walls; Rothenburg monastery museum with caryatids of virtues and vices.

listings.title: Rick Steves' Europe
listings.episode_title: North England's Lake District and Durham
listings.description: Rick Steves' guidebooks, public-radio program and numerous television series have made him an essential resource for travelers wishing to explore Europe. This program finds the knowledgeable host offering globetrotters a fresh perspective on lodgings, transportation and places to visit on their journeys. One thing that hasn't changed, however, is Steves' belief that travelers should become "temporary locals," exploring not only major cities and the usual sites, but out-of-the-way locales that often produce the most authentic, and enjoyable, experiences of a trip.
listings.episode_description: Hiking through the Cumbria Lake District; cricket; hiking Hadrian's Wall; Durham Cathedral.

listings.title: The Best of the Joy of Painting
listings.description: This series of episodes culled from the vast library of the late Bob Ross ("The Joy of Painting") features the soft-spoken host sharing his painting techniques, including his "wet-on-wet" technique, and creating some of his best-loved scenes. From a cabin in the majestic mountains or a covered bride to an owl in a country barn or an autumnal forest scene, Ross creates a complete work of art in each episode -- many of which feature his trademark "happy little clouds." His soothing tone and words of encouragement inspire those painting along at home, and entrance those just watching to see him create his nature scenes.
listings.episode_description: A tranquil valley lake.

listings.description: "New Scandinavian Cooking" is a culinary show that isn't filmed in a kitchen or TV studio, which is common with most shows of the genre. The series is filmed on a variety of locations throughout Scandinavia, offering a visual tour of Northern European cuisine, culture and history. In each episode, recipes are prepared featuring locally sourced ingredients, ranging from berries and mushrooms to cod and mussels.
listings.episode_description: Oysters and wild scallops; trout tartar and smoked trout served with a summer salad; trout burger with onion compote and coleslaw.

Each episode deals with a specific staple, what he refers to as a Master Recipe. He demonstrates how to make that one staple, then he shares recipes that use that particular staple. Whether it's a bittersweet chocolate ganache, from which he creates souffle cakes and an Asian banana split, or flavorful chicken broth he then uses to prepare ginger-poached chicken breast and hot and sour shrimp soup, the chef shares recipes and tricks for the beginning cook as well as the accomplished kitchen pro.

The series has been recognized for its journalism excellence with many honors, including a 2008 Peabody Award.

listings.description: Opera lovers, rejoice! If you can't make it to New York to see a performance at the Metropolitan Opera, the next best thing to being there is to see one of its Saturday matinees broadcast on PBS. Originally aired as part of its "Great Performances" series, the programs got their own title in 2006. With operatic standards like "Aida," "The Barber of Seville" and "Turandot," and performances by some of opera's biggest names, including Reneé Flemming, Placido Domingo and Anna Netrebko, the series brings the best of modern opera into American homes.

listings.title: Kevin Belton's New Orleans Celebrations
listings.description: Chef Kevin Belton's new cooking series -- inspired by the vibrant festivals of New Orleans and its surrounding region -- showcases the unique food and multicultural heritage of the city. In his courtyard kitchen at WYES-TV studios, Belton prepares some of the best food booth favorites unique to the Big Easy, including breakfast jambalaya, a shrimp and crab burger, fried oyster po'boy sandwiches and Creole brined chicken. This 26-episode series also features segments with food vendors and festival-goers on location at the Oyster Festival, the French Market Creole Tomato Festival, Bastille Day Fete, Satchmo SummerFest and others.

Each episode features a single Mexican food, ranging from familiar ingredients like vanilla to mysterious grains used by the Aztecs. Season 8 explores simple and delectable dishes from both Mexico and the United States, including street food, a seafood feast, taco recipes, lobster recipes, and a breakfast based on Sinaloan classics.

listings.title: Rick Steves' Europe

This program finds the knowledgeable host offering globetrotters a fresh perspective on lodgings, transportation and places to visit on their journeys. One thing that hasn't changed, however, is Steves' belief that travelers should become "temporary locals," exploring not only major cities and the usual sites, but out-of-the-way locales that often produce the most authentic, and enjoyable, experiences of a trip.
listings.episode_description: Rick Steves offers practical advice on how to have a fun and affordable trip to Europe. Sites include Germany, Italy, the Swiss Alps, Paris and London.

listings.title: The Best of the Joy of Painting
listings.description: This series of episodes culled from the vast library of the late Bob Ross ("The Joy of Painting") features the soft-spoken host sharing his painting techniques, including his "wet-on-wet" technique, and creating some of his best-loved scenes. From a cabin in the majestic mountains or a covered bride to an owl in a country barn or an autumnal forest scene, Ross creates a complete work of art in each episode -- many of which feature his trademark "happy little clouds." His soothing tone and words of encouragement inspire those painting along at home, and entrance those just watching to see him create his nature scenes.
listings.episode_description: An early morning light is reflected in the misty stillness of forest waters.

Happy Yoga, as she calls it, is a modified program using chairs that allows people of any age or physical condition to be able to benefit from yoga. "Happy Yoga" features Starr performing the chair exercises outside, utilizing serene backdrops that showcase Mother Nature's beauty.

Using gadgets and following clues, the team solves math mysteries and any other problem that comes their way.
listings.episode_description: Buzz and Delete enlist the CyberSquad to figure out why the water supply at Mount Bear Fresh Water Spa has stopped flowing.

listings.description: This landmark series, which first premiered in 1987, documents the history of the civil rights movement in America. listings.description: "Frontline" offers an unflinching and compelling look at complex, vital and often-controversial subjects. Each broadcast consists of a long-form news documentary. Topics run the gamut -- from Bernie Madoff's intricate fraud and prisoner abuse at Abu Ghraib, to AIDs, racial issues and Wal-Mart's effect on the U.S. economy.
listings.episode_description: Tracing the rise of an online network known as Terrorgram, used to spread extremism and violence.

listings.description: Yoga can be challenging, especially for beginners who may be apprehensive about trying something that they think is too daunting. Wanting to help those who are new to the exercise, fitness instructor Sarah Starr created an easier routine. Happy Yoga, as she calls it, is a modified program using chairs that allows people of any age or physical condition to be able to benefit from yoga. "Happy Yoga" features Starr performing the chair exercises outside, utilizing serene backdrops that showcase Mother Nature's beauty.
listings.episode_description: A modified yoga practice focuses on opening the hips and elongating the spine while increasing circulation.

Using gadgets and following clues, the team solves math mysteries and any other problem that comes their way.

In each episode, celebrities view ancestral histories, sometimes learn of connections to famous/infamous people, discover secrets, and share the emotional experience with viewers. listings.description: Consistently stunning documentaries transport viewers to far-flung locations ranging from the torrid African plains to the chilly splendors of icy Antarctica. A comic book based on the show, meant to be used an as educational tool for kids, was briefly distributed to museums and schools at no cost in the mid-2000s.
listings.episode_description: Grizzly 399 attempts to raise an unusually large litter in Grand Teton National Park, becoming a hopeful symbol of the survival and preservation of wildlife.

Inspired by the BBC documentary program "Horizons, " the U.S. series frequently features interviews with scientists directly involved in the topic at hand, and sometimes even boasts footage of a particular discovery.
listings.episode_description: Scientists discover the oldest DNA ever found and reveal the genes of long-extinct creatures that once thrived in the Arctic.

listings.description: Experts use modern forensic techniques to shed new light on historical mysteries such as the sinking of the Andrea Doria and the riddle of whether a weather or geological event of some kind might have triggered the Dark Ages.

listings.title: Cook's Country
listings.description: Hosts Bridget Lancaster and Julia Collin Davison offer a practical, no-nonsense and scientific approach to making a wide range of American recipes, from barbecue chicken thighs to Mississippi mud pie to parmesan potatoes. The hosts are joined by test cooks Ashley Moore, Bryan Roof, Christie Morrison, Lawman Johnson, and Natalie Estrada. Episodes include equipment recommendations for the home cook, taste tests and origins for new recipes such as Southern-style smothered chicken, grilled bourbon steaks and many more.
listings.episode_description: Mana'eesh za'atar; baba ghanoush; different eggplants; roasted beets with lemon-tahini dressing.

listings.title: Pati's Mexican Table
listings.description: Chef Pati Jinich introduces authentic Mexican flavors, colors and textures into American kitchens. Each episode features a single Mexican food, ranging from familiar ingredients like vanilla to mysterious grains used by the Aztecs. Season 8 explores simple and delectable dishes from both Mexico and the United States, including street food, a seafood feast, taco recipes, lobster recipes, and a breakfast based on Sinaloan classics.
listings.episode_description: Simple, inexpensive recipes that college students can make for themselves; a series of simple cooking strategies.

listings.title: How She Rolls
listings.description: Carrie Morey balances business and family life in Charleston, S.C.
listings.episode_description: Carrie goes on the road for her first speaking tour; Caroline's Cakes; decorating with caramel icing; food finds at a local grocer in Greenville, S.C.

listings.title: This Old House
listings.description: This Emmy-winning home-improvement series takes the mystery and fright factors out of remodeling and carpentry chores.
listings.episode_description: Installing a five-layer flitch beam; a tree company attaches a cable on an old hemlock for support; pruning an overgrown crabapple tree; preparing a footing to support the corner chimney.

listings.title: J Schwanke's Life in Bloom
listings.description: Fourth-generation florist, author and floral educator J Schwanke hosts this series about flower arrangement, design and instruction. Aiming to help viewers have fun with flowers, the program shows how to incorporate flowers into homes and everyday life. The series also includes tours of flower farms, greenhouses, markets, festivals and special events around the world. Some segments include a visit to a succulent farm, tulip-inspired recipes, using fruit and flowers in arrangements, recipes and crafts and creating an orchid wreath.

listings.title: Rick Steves' Europe
listings.description: Rick Steves' guidebooks, public-radio program and numerous television series have made him an essential resource for travelers wishing to explore Europe. This program finds the knowledgeable host offering globetrotters a fresh perspective on lodgings, transportation and places to visit on their journeys. One thing that hasn't changed, however, is Steves' belief that travelers should become "temporary locals," exploring not only major cities and the usual sites, but out-of-the-way locales that often produce the most authentic, and enjoyable, experiences of a trip.
listings.episode_description: Aerial view of Cappadocia; underground city; circumcision party; exploring troglodyte ghost towns; shopping for sheep; the modern capital of Ankara.

listings.title: The Best of the Joy of Painting
listings.description: This series of episodes culled from the vast library of the late Bob Ross ("The Joy of Painting") features the soft-spoken host sharing his painting techniques, including his "wet-on-wet" technique, and creating some of his best-loved scenes. From a cabin in the majestic mountains or a covered bride to an owl in a country barn or an autumnal forest scene, Ross creates a complete work of art in each episode -- many of which feature his trademark "happy little clouds." His soothing tone and words of encouragement inspire those painting along at home, and entrance those just watching to see him create his nature scenes.
listings.episode_description: A mountain scene in a faux matte.

Topics run the gamut -- from Bernie Madoff's intricate fraud and prisoner abuse at Abu Ghraib, to AIDs, racial issues and Wal-Mart's effect on the U.S. economy.
listings.episode_description: Tracing the rise of an online network known as Terrorgram, used to spread extremism and violence.

listings.episode_description: Journalist Jeffrey Frank.

listings.episode_description: The coming-of-age story of Ashley Chea, a Cambodian American basketball prodigy in Southern California who overcomes injury, racial and class differences to become her own person and leave a legacy behind.

listings.title: In Julia's Kitchen With Master Chefs

listings.episode_description: Monique Barbeau prepares gravlax cured with tequila and lime, and dill pancakes.

listings.title: Happy Yoga With Sarah Starr

Wanting to help those who are new to the exercise, fitness instructor Sarah Starr created an easier routine. Happy Yoga, as she calls it, is a modified program using chairs that allows people of any age or physical condition to be able to benefit from yoga. "Happy Yoga" features Starr performing the chair exercises outside, utilizing serene backdrops that showcase Mother Nature's beauty.
listings.episode_description: A modified yoga practice focuses on opening the hips and elongating the spine while increasing circulation.

listings.title: Classical Stretch: By Essentrics
listings.description: Miranda Esmonde-White offers an exercise program for people of all ages and fitness levels.
listings.episode_description: A full-body strengthening workout builds endurance and power.

Using gadgets and following clues, the team solves math mysteries and any other problem that comes their way.
listings.episode_description: Shari Spotter and her team create a budget for their new film, but the Hacker complicates their efforts.

listings.episode_description: Search for the endangered orangutan in Borneo.

Every day Daniel puts on his red sweater, ties his shoes, and invites a new generation of preschoolers into the Neighborhood of Make-Believe. Daniel shares his daily adventures with pals O the Owl, Katerina Kittycat, Prince Wednesday and Miss Elaina. With the help of Daniel and his friends, preschoolers have fun and learn practical skills necessary for growing and developing.
listings.episode_description: Daniel finds out he is going to be a big brother; Daniel wants to help prepare the baby's room but struggles with having to give up his old things for his new sibling.

Big Bird leads a cast of characters teaching children numbers, colors and the alphabet. Bert and Ernie, Oscar the Grouch and Grover are just a few of the other creatures involved in this show, set on a city street full of valuable learning opportunities.

listings.episode_description: Rosie and Javi both want to be in charge of the sandbox, so the kids hold an election to choose a president; Rosie and friends try to save the dino parade.

listings.episode_description: An argument between Xavier and Yadina ends badly, but Maya Angelou helps the siblings find a way to forgive each other; Frederick Douglass helps Xavier when he becomes frustrated with his schoolwork.
